label: Vietnamese note
backstory: The North Vietnam government, previously known as the Viet Minh, introduced dong as its currency in 1946, which replaced the French Indochinese piastre. The currency was revaluated in 1951 and 1959 at the rate of 100 to 1 and 1000 to 1, respectively.
